      • isCustom

        default boolean isCustom()

        If the bullet uses a custom rendering method.

        For performance, if the bullet can be rendered using only drawEmbedded(float, float, float, float), it should be rendered as a combined bullet instead.

        Returns:
        true if a custom rendering method is being used, false otherwise.
        See Also:
        render(float, float, float, float, BulletState, Graphics, float, float), isCombined(), renderEmbedded(float, float, float, float, BulletState, Graphics, Image, float, float)

      • render

        default void render(float px,
                    float py,
                    float xv,
                    float yv,
                    BulletState state,
                    org.newdawn.slick.Graphics g,
                    float sx,
                    float sy)

        Renders a custom bullet. When this method is called no texture is currently bound.

        For performance, if the bullet can be rendered using only drawEmbedded(float, float, float, float), it should be rendered as a combined bullet instead.

        Parameters:
        px - The player X position.
        py - The player Y position.
        xv - The player X velocity.
        yv - The player Y velocity.
        state - The current bullet state.
        g - The current graphics context.
        sx - The X position of the bullet on the screen.
        sy - The Y position of the bullet on the screen.
        See Also:
        isCustom(), isCombined(), renderEmbedded(float, float, float, float, BulletState, Graphics, Image, float, float)

      • isCombined

        default boolean isCombined()

        Indicates that a bullet may make multiple draw calls but still use drawEmbedded(float, float, float, float)

        This system has greater performance than isCustom() and render(float, float, float, float, BulletState, Graphics, float, float) but it requires that textures are bound and unbound.

        Returns:
        true if a combined rendering method is being used, false otherwise.
        See Also:
        render(float, float, float, float, BulletState, Graphics, float, float), renderEmbedded(float, float, float, float, BulletState, Graphics, Image, float, float), isCustom()

      • renderEmbedded

        default org.newdawn.slick.Image renderEmbedded(float px,
                                               float py,
                                               float xv,
                                               float yv,
                                               BulletState state,
                                               org.newdawn.slick.Graphics g,
                                               org.newdawn.slick.Image current,
                                               float sx,
                                               float sy)

        Renders a bullet using embedded methods.

        This system has greater performance than isCustom() and render(float, float, float, float, BulletState, Graphics, float, float) but it requires that textures are bound and unbound.

        Non-embedded drawing can be done provided the texture is unbound then bound again as shown below.

        if (current != null) current.endUse();
        ...Do something...
        if (current != null) current.startUse();

        To change the texture if should be done similar to what is shown below. The method shown below also allows for texture atlasing to be used which can improve performance.

        • img - The image you want to change to.
        if (current != TextureMap.getSheet(img)) {
            if (current != null) current.endUse();
            current = TextureMap.getSheet(img);
            current.startUse();
        }
        Parameters:
        px - The X position of the player.
        py - The Y position of the player.
        xv - The X velocity of the player.
        yv - The Y velocity of the player.
        state - The current bullet state.
        g - The current graphics context.
        current - The current texture or null if no texture is bound.
        sx - The X position of the bullet on the screen.
        sy - The Y position of the bullet on the screen.
        Returns:
        This should return current including any changes made to the bound texture.
        See Also:
        TextureMap, TextureMap.getSheet(Image), render(float, float, float, float, BulletState, Graphics, float, float), isCombined(), isCustom()
